The paper discusses a novel program repair technique for Deep Neural Networks (DNNs), which falls under the category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The technique involves using Particle Swarm Optimization (PSO) to optimize the localised neural weights, which is a search-based approach, and hence, can also be classified under Software Engineering (cs.SE). The paper also mentions the use of sensitivity-based fault localization, which is a technique commonly used in control systems (cs.SY) and neural networks (cs.NE). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.LG, cs.SE, cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.SY, in that order.
